{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Baby feeding study \u2014 Colab notebook\n",
    "\n",
    "End-to-end data cleaning + exploratory analysis for the multi-sheet `baby.xlsx` dataset\n",
    "(infant feeding study: behavioral binaries + valence/arousal time series, 20 babies).\n",
    "\n",
    "**What this notebook does:**\n",
    "1. Uploads `baby.xlsx` (Colab file picker)\n",
    "2. Loads & concatenates 20 patient sheets\n",
    "3. **Tells you exactly what it found and what's broken in the raw data**\n",
    "4. Standardizes time strings, day codes, behavioral binaries, valence/arousal\n",
    "5. **Reports row drops, NaN counts, and per-baby completeness at every step**\n",
    "6. Deep dive on `lo_consume` \u2014 the central behavioral outcome\n",
    "7. Normalizes (z-score + min-max)\n",
    "8. Pre-TDA visualizations (PCA, UMAP)\n",
    "9. Downloads the cleaned outputs\n",
    "\n",
    "**Cleaning conventions (locked in upfront):**\n",
    "- One row per `(patient_id, day)`\n",
    "- All missing/failed tokens (`FIT_FAILED`, `NA`, `-`, `S/I`, `None`, `''`) \u2192 `NaN`\n",
    "  with parallel `*_was_missing` / `*_fit_failed` indicator columns\n",
    "- `S\u00ed, poco` \u2192 ordinal `0.5` (No=0, S\u00ed=1)\n",
    "- Column drop threshold by missingness: 0.60 (configurable in \u00a76)\n",
    "\n",
    "Just run the cells top to bottom.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## \u00a70 \u2014 Setup\n",
    "\n",
    "Install UMAP (the rest of the stack is preinstalled in Colab)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!pip install -q umap-learn"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import re\n",
    "import unicodedata\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.set_theme(style=\"whitegrid\", context=\"notebook\")\n",
    "pd.set_option(\"display.max_columns\", 80)\n",
    "pd.set_option(\"display.width\", 200)\n",
    "plt.rcParams[\"figure.dpi\"] = 100\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## \u00a71 \u2014 Upload `baby.xlsx`\n",
    "\n",
    "Run the cell, click *Choose Files*, pick `baby.xlsx`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "try:\n",
    "    from google.colab import files\n",
    "    uploaded = files.upload()\n",
    "    INPUT_PATH = list(uploaded.keys())[0]\n",
    "    print(f\"\\nFile loaded: {INPUT_PATH}\")\n",
    "except ImportError:\n",
    "    INPUT_PATH = \"baby.xlsx\"   # local fallback\n",
    "    print(f\"Not in Colab \u2014 using local file: {INPUT_PATH}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "OUTPUT_DIR = Path(\"./cleaned_outputs\")\n",
    "OUTPUT_DIR.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## \u00a72 \u2014 Load and inspect raw data\n",
    "\n",
    "What we'll do:\n",
    "- Open every `ID*` sheet\n",
    "- Collapse the two-row header into clean snake_case column names\n",
    "- Concatenate into one long DataFrame (one row per patient-day)\n",
    "- **Report exactly what we loaded**\n",
    "\n",
    "The standard schema is 26 columns; ID3 has 8 extras (a 3rd test event)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Column schema \u2014 position-based mapping\n",
    "STANDARD_COLUMNS = {\n",
    "    0:  \"day\",\n",
    "    1:  \"time_total\",       # Spanish \"T\u00b0\" here actually means \"tiempo\" (time), not temperature\n",
    "    2:  \"time_test1\",\n",
    "    3:  \"time_test2\",\n",
    "    4:  \"rejects\",          # Rechaza\n",
    "    5:  \"cries\",            # Llora\n",
    "    6:  \"touches\",          # Lo toca\n",
    "    7:  \"tries\",            # Lo prueba\n",
    "    8:  \"consumes\",         # Lo consume  <-- our focal variable\n",
    "    9:  \"valence_start\",\n",
    "    10: \"arousal_start\",\n",
    "    11: \"valence_test1_before\",\n",
    "    12: \"valence_test1_during\",\n",
    "    13: \"valence_test1_after\",\n",
    "    14: \"valence_test2_before\",\n",
    "    15: \"valence_test2_during\",\n",
    "    16: \"valence_test2_after\",\n",
    "    17: \"arousal_test1_before\",\n",
    "    18: \"arousal_test1_during\",\n",
    "    19: \"arousal_test1_after\",\n",
    "    20: \"arousal_test2_before\",\n",
    "    21: \"arousal_test2_during\",\n",
    "    22: \"arousal_test2_after\",\n",
    "    23: \"valence_end\",\n",
    "    24: \"arousal_end\",\n",
    "    25: \"comments\",\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# ID3-only extras (cols 28-33)\n",
    "EXTRA_COLUMNS_ID3 = {\n",
    "    28: \"valence_test3_before\",\n",
    "    29: \"valence_test3_during\",\n",
    "    30: \"valence_test3_after\",\n",
    "    31: \"arousal_test3_before\",\n",
    "    32: \"arousal_test3_during\",\n",
    "    33: \"arousal_test3_after\",\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "TIME_COLS = (\"time_total\", \"time_test1\", \"time_test2\")\n",
    "BEHAVIOR_COLS = (\"rejects\", \"cries\", \"touches\", \"tries\", \"consumes\")\n",
    "VA_COLS_BASE = (\n",
    "    \"valence_start\", \"arousal_start\",\n",
    "    \"valence_test1_before\", \"valence_test1_during\", \"valence_test1_after\",\n",
    "    \"valence_test2_before\", \"valence_test2_during\", \"valence_test2_after\",\n",
    "    \"arousal_test1_before\", \"arousal_test1_during\", \"arousal_test1_after\",\n",
    "    \"arousal_test2_before\", \"arousal_test2_during\", \"arousal_test2_after\",\n",
    "    \"valence_end\", \"arousal_end\",\n",
    ")\n",
    "VA_COLS_EXTRA = tuple(EXTRA_COLUMNS_ID3.values())\n",
    "VA_COLS = VA_COLS_BASE + VA_COLS_EXTRA\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def load_sheet(xlsx_path, sheet_name):\n",
    "    raw = pd.read_excel(xlsx_path, sheet_name=sheet_name, header=None)\n",
    "    data = raw.iloc[2:].reset_index(drop=True)   # drop the two header rows\n",
    "\n",
    "    n_cols = data.shape[1]\n",
    "    names = []\n",
    "    for i in range(n_cols):\n",
    "        if i in STANDARD_COLUMNS:\n",
    "            names.append(STANDARD_COLUMNS[i])\n",
    "        elif i in EXTRA_COLUMNS_ID3:\n",
    "            names.append(EXTRA_COLUMNS_ID3[i])\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            names.append(f\"extra_{i}\")\n",
    "    data.columns = names\n",
    "    data = data.loc[:, [c for c in data.columns if not c.startswith(\"extra_\")]]\n",
    "\n",
    "    n_before = len(data)\n",
    "    data = data[data[\"day\"].notna()].copy()      # drop trailing-blank rows\n",
    "    n_dropped = n_before - len(data)\n",
    "\n",
    "    data.insert(0, \"patient_id\", sheet_name)\n",
    "    return data, n_dropped\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def load_all_patients(xlsx_path):\n",
    "    xl = pd.ExcelFile(xlsx_path)\n",
    "    patient_sheets = [s for s in xl.sheet_names if re.fullmatch(r\"ID\\d+\", s)]\n",
    "    frames = []\n",
    "    total_dropped = 0\n",
    "    per_sheet_report = []\n",
    "    for s in patient_sheets:\n",
    "        df, dropped = load_sheet(xlsx_path, s)\n",
    "        frames.append(df)\n",
    "        total_dropped += dropped\n",
    "        per_sheet_report.append((s, len(df), dropped))\n",
    "    combined = pd.concat(frames, ignore_index=True, sort=False)\n",
    "    return combined, per_sheet_report, total_dropped\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "raw, per_sheet_report, n_blank_rows_dropped = load_all_patients(INPUT_PATH)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
    "print(\"LOAD REPORT\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
    "print(f\"Patient sheets found:       {len(per_sheet_report)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Total rows after load:      {len(raw):,}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Blank trailing rows dropped during load: {n_blank_rows_dropped}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Columns in concatenated frame: {raw.shape[1]}\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print(\"Rows per patient:\")\n",
    "report_df = pd.DataFrame(per_sheet_report, columns=[\"patient_id\", \"n_rows\", \"blanks_dropped\"])\n",
    "print(report_df.to_string(index=False))\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# A peek at the actual data\n",
    "print(\"First few rows:\")\n",
    "raw.head()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## \u00a73 \u2014 Pre-clean audit: what's wrong with the raw data\n",
    "\n",
    "The raw file has multiple problems we need to see before fixing:\n",
    "- Inconsistent yes/no encodings (`S\u00ed`, `Si`, `SI`, `si`, `No`, `No `, `no`, `NA`, `-`, etc.)\n",
    "- Time columns stored as a mix of numbers, `HH:MM:SS.mmm` strings, and malformed entries\n",
    "- Multiple \"missing\" tokens (`NA`, `N/A`, `S/I`, `-`, empty, `None`, `FIT_FAILED`)\n",
    "- Some day cells like `1E` instead of plain integers"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
    "print(\"DTYPE AUDIT (raw)\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
    "print(raw.dtypes.value_counts())\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print(\"Everything is 'object' because of mixed string/number cells. We'll fix that.\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
    "print(\"ENCODING CHAOS \u2014 unique values in the 5 behavioral columns\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
    "for col in BEHAVIOR_COLS:\n",
    "    unique_vals = sorted({repr(x) for x in raw[col].dropna().unique()})\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n{col} ({len(unique_vals)} distinct values):\")\n",
    "    print(\"  \", unique_vals)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
    "print(\"TIME COLUMN CHAOS \u2014 sample of non-numeric entries\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
    "for col in TIME_COLS:\n",
    "    bad = raw[col][raw[col].apply(lambda x: x is not None and not isinstance(x, (int, float)))]\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n{col}: {len(bad)} non-numeric entries (sample of 12):\")\n",
    "    print(\"  \", sorted(bad.astype(str).unique())[:12])\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
    "print(\"MISSING-VALUE TOKENS \u2014 how many different ways is 'missing' written?\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
    "\n",
    "missing_like = set()\n",
    "for col in raw.columns:\n",
    "    if col == \"patient_id\":\n",
    "        continue\n",
    "    for v in raw[col].dropna().unique():\n",
    "        s = str(v).strip().lower()\n",
    "        if s in (\"na\", \"n/a\", \"s/i\", \"-\", \"fit_failed\", \"\"):\n",
    "            missing_like.add(repr(v))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Found {len(missing_like)} distinct missing-equivalent tokens:\")\n",
    "for t in sorted(missing_like):\n",
    "    print(f\"   {t}\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Pre-cleaning NaN count\n",
    "total_cells = raw.size\n",
    "nan_count = raw.isna().sum().sum()\n",
    "print(f\"Total cells in raw frame:   {total_cells:,}\")\n",
    "print(f\"True NaN (None) cells:      {nan_count:,}  ({nan_count/total_cells:.1%})\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nBut remember: many cells contain string-form 'missing' tokens that are NOT yet NaN.\")\n",
    "print(f\"After cleaning, the true NaN count will be much higher \u2014 and accurate.\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## \u00a74 \u2014 Standardize\n",
    "\n",
    "For each column type we apply the right parser:\n",
    "- **Time** (`time_total`, `time_test1/2`): floats kept as-is; `HH:MM:SS.mmm` parsed to seconds; malformed \u2192 NaN\n",
    "- **Day**: numeric kept; suffixes like `1E` split into `day=1, day_flag='E'`\n",
    "- **Behavioral binaries**: case/accent normalized \u2192 ordinal {No=0, S\u00ed poco=0.5, S\u00ed=1}; missing \u2192 NaN\n",
    "- **Valence/Arousal**: floats kept; `FIT_FAILED` \u2192 NaN + boolean indicator; other missing \u2192 NaN + indicator"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "MISSING_TOKENS = {\"\", \"-\", \"na\", \"n/a\", \"s/i\", \"nan\", \"none\"}\n",
    "FIT_FAILED_TOKEN = \"fit_failed\"\n",
    "_TIME_RE = re.compile(r\"^(\\d{1,2}):(\\d{1,2}):(\\d{1,2}(?:\\.\\d+)?)$\")\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def _strip_accents(s):\n",
    "    return \"\".join(\n",
    "        c for c in unicodedata.normalize(\"NFKD\", s) if not unicodedata.combining(c)\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def _normalize_token(x):\n",
    "    if x is None or (isinstance(x, float) and np.isnan(x)):\n",
    "        return \"\"\n",
    "    return _strip_accents(str(x).strip().lower())\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def parse_time_to_seconds(value):\n",
    "    if isinstance(value, (int, float)) and not (isinstance(value, float) and np.isnan(value)):\n",
    "        return float(value)\n",
    "    tok = _normalize_token(value)\n",
    "    if tok in MISSING_TOKENS or tok == FIT_FAILED_TOKEN:\n",
    "        return np.nan\n",
    "    m = _TIME_RE.match(tok)\n",
    "    if m:\n",
    "        h, mnt, sec = m.groups()\n",
    "        return int(h)*3600 + int(mnt)*60 + float(sec)\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        return float(tok.replace(\",\", \".\"))\n",
    "    except ValueError:\n",
    "        return np.nan\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def parse_day(value):\n",
    "    if value is None or (isinstance(value, float) and np.isnan(value)):\n",
    "        return (np.nan, None)\n",
    "    s = str(value).strip()\n",
    "    m = re.match(r\"^(\\d+)([A-Za-z]*)$\", s)\n",
    "    if not m:\n",
    "        return (np.nan, s if s else None)\n",
    "    num, suffix = m.groups()\n",
    "    return (float(num), suffix if suffix else None)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def parse_yesno(value):\n",
    "    tok = _normalize_token(value)\n",
    "    if tok in MISSING_TOKENS:\n",
    "        return np.nan\n",
    "    if tok == \"no\":\n",
    "        return 0.0\n",
    "    if \"poco\" in tok:\n",
    "        return 0.5\n",
    "    if tok in (\"si\", \"s\u00ed\"):\n",
    "        return 1.0\n",
    "    return np.nan\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def parse_va(value):\n",
    "    if isinstance(value, (int, float)) and not (isinstance(value, float) and np.isnan(value)):\n",
    "        return (float(value), False, False)\n",
    "    tok = _normalize_token(value)\n",
    "    if tok == FIT_FAILED_TOKEN:\n",
    "        return (np.nan, True, False)\n",
    "    if tok in MISSING_TOKENS:\n",
    "        return (np.nan, False, True)\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        return (float(tok.replace(\",\", \".\")), False, False)\n",
    "    except ValueError:\n",
    "        return (np.nan, False, True)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def standardize(df):\n",
    "    out = df.copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "    # day\n",
    "    parsed = out[\"day\"].map(parse_day)\n",
    "    out[\"day\"] = parsed.map(lambda t: t[0])\n",
    "    out[\"day_flag\"] = parsed.map(lambda t: t[1])\n",
    "\n",
    "    # time columns\n",
    "    for col in TIME_COLS:\n",
    "        if col in out.columns:\n",
    "            out[f\"{col}_was_missing\"] = out[col].map(lambda v: _normalize_token(v) in MISSING_TOKENS)\n",
    "            out[col] = out[col].map(parse_time_to_seconds)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # behavior binaries\n",
    "    for col in BEHAVIOR_COLS:\n",
    "        if col in out.columns:\n",
    "            out[f\"{col}_was_missing\"] = out[col].map(lambda v: _normalize_token(v) in MISSING_TOKENS)\n",
    "            out[col] = out[col].map(parse_yesno)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # valence / arousal\n",
    "    for col in VA_COLS:\n",
    "        if col not in out.columns:\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "        parsed_va = out[col].map(parse_va)\n",
    "        out[col] = parsed_va.map(lambda t: t[0])\n",
    "        out[f\"{col}_fit_failed\"] = parsed_va.map(lambda t: t[1])\n",
    "        out[f\"{col}_was_missing\"] = parsed_va.map(lambda t: t[2])\n",
    "\n",
    "    return out\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "cleaned = standardize(raw)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Drop rows where every numeric feature is NaN (truly empty rows after cleaning)\n",
    "feature_cols = [c for c in cleaned.columns\n",
    "                if c not in (\"patient_id\", \"day_flag\", \"comments\")\n",
    "                and not c.endswith((\"_was_missing\", \"_fit_failed\"))]\n",
    "\n",
    "n_before = len(cleaned)\n",
    "cleaned = cleaned.dropna(subset=feature_cols, how=\"all\").reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "n_after = len(cleaned)\n",
    "empty_rows_dropped = n_before - n_after\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
    "print(\"CLEANING REPORT\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
    "print(f\"Rows in:                          {n_before:,}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Rows dropped (all-NaN features):  {empty_rows_dropped}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Rows out:                         {n_after:,}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Total columns (incl. indicators): {cleaned.shape[1]}\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Sanity check \u2014 behavioral columns are now ordinal {0, 0.5, 1, NaN}\n",
    "print(\"Behavioral binary value counts AFTER standardization:\")\n",
    "for col in BEHAVIOR_COLS:\n",
    "    counts = cleaned[col].value_counts(dropna=False).to_dict()\n",
    "    print(f\"  {col:>10}: {counts}\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Sanity check \u2014 time columns are now numeric seconds\n",
    "print(\"\\nTime columns AFTER standardization (.describe):\")\n",
    "cleaned[list(TIME_COLS)].describe().round(2)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## \u00a75 \u2014 Post-clean audit: what does the data look like now?\n",
    "\n",
    "The cleaned NaN counts are now the *real* NaN counts (every messy token has been\n",
    "collapsed to actual `NaN`)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Per-column NaN summary\n",
    "miss = cleaned[feature_cols].isna().sum().to_frame(\"n_nan\")\n",
    "miss[\"pct_nan\"] = cleaned[feature_cols].isna().mean()\n",
    "miss = miss.sort_values(\"pct_nan\", ascending=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "total_feature_cells = cleaned[feature_cols].size\n",
    "total_nan = cleaned[feature_cols].isna().sum().sum()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
    "print(\"POST-CLEAN NaN AUDIT\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
    "print(f\"Feature cells total:  {total_feature_cells:,}\")\n",
    "print(f\"NaN cells:            {total_nan:,}  ({total_nan/total_feature_cells:.1%})\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print(miss.to_string())\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Visual: missingness bar chart with the 0.60 threshold marked\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 7))\n",
    "miss[\"pct_nan\"].sort_values().plot(kind=\"barh\", ax=ax, color=\"#4a90e2\")\n",
    "ax.axvline(0.60, color=\"red\", linestyle=\"--\", label=\"drop threshold = 0.60\")\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"% missing\")\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Column missingness (post-cleaning)\")\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Visual: missingness heatmap (rows = patient-days, cols = features)\n",
