    "- `X_features_zscore.csv` \u2014 z-scored numeric matrix\n",
    "- `X_features_minmax.csv` \u2014 min-max scaled (good for Mapper)\n",
    "- `X_indicators.csv` \u2014 `*_fit_failed` / `*_was_missing` booleans, useful as auxiliary features\n",
    "- `X_meta.csv` \u2014 patient_id, day, comments for trajectory analyses\n",
    "- `cleaned_long.csv` \u2014 everything together, for re-deriving any of the above\n",
    "\n",
    "For Mapper / persistent homology with `giotto-tda` or `kmapper`, feed `X_features_zscore`\n",
    "and use `consumes` as a coloring lens to see if behavioral acceptance maps to topology."
